---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Masthead from '../components/Masthead.astro';
import SiteFooter from '../components/SiteFooter.astro';
---
<Base
  title="About Tijori — our data partner"
  description="Filings is built on data from Tijori, the Indian-equities research platform behind Tijori Finance and the Tijori Stack AI toolkit. What they do, and what we use."
>
  <Masthead />
  <main>
    <article class="prose-page">
      <header>
        <div class="kicker"><span>Data partner</span></div>
        <h1 class="page-title">Built on Tijori.</h1>
      </header>

      <hr class="rule" />

      <p>
        Most of what you read here begins as data from <a href="https://www.tijorifinance.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Tijori</a>.
        The filings we summarise, the company fundamentals in the snapshot boxes, the
        concall notes, the market signals — the raw material is theirs. We think the
        people who built that deserve a plain word of credit, and our readers deserve to
        know where the numbers come from.
      </p>
      <p>
        Tijori is a Bengaluru company, founded in 2016 and backed by Zerodha, that has
        spent the better part of a decade doing the unglamorous work of structuring
        Indian-equity data. That groundwork is what lets a small publication like this one
        move fast without inventing the data layer from scratch.
      </p>

      <h2>Tijori Finance — the research platform</h2>
      <p>
        <a href="https://www.tijorifinance.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Tijori Finance</a>
        is a research and tracking platform for Indian listed companies. Its distinctive bet
        is on <em>operational</em> and alternative data — the kind pulled out of annual reports
        rather than off the price ticker. Market share, revenue mix, geographic exposure,
        store counts, capacity, supply-chain detail: the platform indexes thousands of such
        metrics that most screeners simply don't carry, alongside the usual financials,
        shareholding, filings and earnings calls.
      </p>
      <p>The parts of it worth knowing:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://www.tijorifinance.com/in/ideas-dashboard/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Ideas Dashboard</a> — curated screens for finding companies worth a look.</li>
        <li><a href="https://www.tijorifinance.com/filter/popular-queries" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Stock Screener</a> — natural-language filtering over the full metric set.</li>
        <li><a href="https://www.tijorifinance.com/results/quarterly-results/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Results Tracker</a> — quarterly results as they're declared.</li>
        <li><a href="https://www.tijorifinance.com/in/markets" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Market Monitor</a> — niche, sector-level indices.</li>
        <li><a href="https://www.tijorifinance.com/in/macro" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Macro Indicators</a> and <a href="https://www.tijorifinance.com/in/raw-materials" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Raw Materials</a> — the backdrop most equity tools ignore.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        It integrates with Zerodha for portfolio tracking, and its data also powers parts of
        Zerodha's own Console. There's a free tier and a premium subscription; a companion
        service, <a href="https://tijorialerts.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Tijori Alerts</a>,
        pushes real-time stock updates over WhatsApp.
      </p>

      <h2>Tijori Stack — the AI toolkit</h2>
      <p>
        <a href="https://www.tijoristack.ai" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Tijori Stack</a> is the
        newer, builder-facing side of the house: a catalogue of AI tools for equity analysis,
        priced pay-as-you-go rather than by seat. Built by the same team, it turns the
        underlying data into things you can act on quickly:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://www.tijoristack.ai/concall-monitor/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Concall Monitor</a> — AI summaries, transcripts and recordings of earnings calls, minutes after they end.</li>
        <li><a href="https://www.tijoristack.ai/report-on-demand/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Report on Demand</a> — generated company reports when you need one.</li>
        <li><a href="https://www.tijoristack.ai/radar/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Radar</a> — signal-spotting across the market.</li>
        <li><a href="https://www.tijoristack.ai/atlas/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Atlas</a> — the wider map of what they track.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What Filings uses</h2>
      <p>
        We lean on Tijori for the filings feed that seeds our notes, company fundamentals for
        the snapshot boxes, the Concall Monitor for earnings-call material, and market signals
        for the briefings. Everything published here is our own editorial work — the reading,
        the judgement, and the words are ours — but the spine of facts beneath it is Tijori's.
        Where a note leans on their data, that's the lineage.
      </p>

      <h2>Find them</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Web — <a href="https://www.tijorifinance.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">tijorifinance.com</a> · <a href="https://www.tijoristack.ai" target="_blank" rel="noopener">tijoristack.ai</a></li>
        <li>X — <a href="https://x.com/Tijori1" target="_blank" rel="noopener">@Tijori1</a> · Instagram — <a href="https://www.instagram.com/tijorifinance/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">@tijorifinance</a></li>
      </ul>
      <p style="color: var(--text-faint); font-size: 14px;">
        Tijori Finance is a product of Tijori Financial Services Private Limited. We're an
        independent publication and not affiliated with Tijori beyond using their data.
      </p>
    </article>
  </main>
  <SiteFooter />
</Base>
